<!-- ENTITY DECLARATIONS -->

<!-- This is where you put any parameter entity that you want to 
change from the same named entity in MIL-STD-38784. For example,
the chapter element in MIL-STD-38784 calls 3 parameter entities:
%chap; %inclus; and %chapatt;.

   Chapter element from MIL-STD-38784:
	<!ELEMENT chapter	- -  (%chap;)  +(%inclus;) >
	<!ATTLIST chapter	%chapatt; >

   Parameter entities from MIL-STD-38784:
	<!ENTITY % chap "title, ((section, (note?, section)+) | para0+)" >

	<!ENTITY % inclus "figure | table | foldout | objmedia" >

	<!ENTITY % chapatt
	"id ID #IMPLIED
	%secur;
	%bodyatt;" >

If you want to change the content of the chapter element, change the 
parameter entities instead of trying to change the element directly.
That way, you can call in the standard elements with the 38784 DTD and
only change what you have to.

This is the %chap parameter entity from your 38314 DTD:

<!ENTITY % chap "(title, contents, ((section, section+) | para0+), foldsect?)" >

The difference from MIL-STD-38784 is that it has zero or one CONTENTS elements 
(which allows an optional chapterized TOC) and allows a FOLDSECT at the back of 
each chapter (MIL-38784 requires all foldouts to be in the back of the book, not
the back of chapters). 38784 would allow a note between sections.  Both require 
two sections if sections are used or one or more paragraphs if sections are not 
used.

If you redefine % chap right after the close comment here, then it will be used 
INSTEAD of the % chap in the following MIL-STD-38784-BV8 dtd. This results in a
standard 38784 manual that also allows a chapterized TOC and foldouts in the rear 
of chapters.
The really illegal thing is that the 38314 DTD changed the SEQLIST and ITEM elements
(which is NOT allowed for military DTDs). I think you should invent new element names 
instead of changing SEQLIST and ITEM because seqlist is not "parametricized" 
(not a parameter entity the way that % chap is a parameter entity) and ITEM uses 
the % text parameter entity which is really inconvienent because of its wide use.
-->
<!ENTITY % chap "(title, contents?, ((section, section+) | para0+), foldsect?)" >

<!ENTITY % m38784STD PUBLIC "-//USA-DOD//DTD 38784STD-BV8//EN" >

